<bibRefCitation id="B2C03B38FCB998CBA5C06FB036E9E9D1" author="Chandler, P. J." journalOrPublisher="Brill, Leiden-Boston-Koeln" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" title="The flat-footed flies (Diptera: Opetiidae and Platypezidae) of Europe. Fauna Entomologica Scandinavica" year="2001">Chandler 2001</bibRefCitation>
), Finland (
<bibRefCitation id="C15B61A7E514BBDE6C295CB654979A3A" author="Stahls, G." journalOrPublisher="Sahlbergia" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" pagination="1 - 6" title="New data on Platypezidae and Opetiidae (Diptera) of Finland" volume="11" year="2006">
<normalizedToken id="7812332AEA7B8D0CD93A4726FDA8FE37" originalValue="Ståhls">Stahls</normalizedToken>
and 
<normalizedToken id="F8E5F15C0C46C040C28749D072B923C2" originalValue="Kahanpää">Kahanpaeae</normalizedToken>
2006
</bibRefCitation>
) and Romania (
<bibRefCitation id="251A5F1BD56734A1B14CA8080DA4F7E9" author="Tkoc, Michal" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" pagination="95 - 118" title="Diversity, distribution and biology of Romanian flat-footed flies (Diptera, Opetiidae and Platypezidae) with taxonomic notes on Callomyia saibhira Chandler" volume="459" year="2014">
<normalizedToken id="13229F636A4A857EA8BABC76834978A3" originalValue="Tkoč">Tkoc</normalizedToken>
and 
<normalizedToken id="4601AA8D1F7B50243D9388D9BBA7AF9F" originalValue="Roháček">Rohacek</normalizedToken>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="970DDC457A25B6E0BCF4649F46799355" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="4510ECBEBC0B8E97E5A5545A056D0803" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175">Ecology</paragraph>
<paragraph id="11F6F7E9E805F7563F0BF13F638DDFE0" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175">
Virtually unknown. Other 
<taxonomicName id="7184D3C2DC2950D50AC7731E9106464F" class="Insecta" family="Platypezidae" genus="Agathomyia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Agathomyia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Agathomyia</taxonomicName>
species assumed to develop internally in polypore fungi (
<bibRefCitation id="1F2DE4FD448239BB02672B40D9B65C1F" author="Chandler, P. J." journalOrPublisher="Brill, Leiden-Boston-Koeln" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" title="The flat-footed flies (Diptera: Opetiidae and Platypezidae) of Europe. Fauna Entomologica Scandinavica" year="2001">Chandler 2001</bibRefCitation>
). In the Czech Republic, adults were registered in pyramidal (emergence) traps (
<bibRefCitation id="6F1240086A941385B2D5AB87C678950E" author="Tkoc, M." editor="Kubik, S." journalOrPublisher="Ceska zemedelska univerzita v Praze, Praha" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" title="Workshop on Biodiversity, Jevany" year="2013">
<normalizedToken id="E957DCCFFCA693A6CBE9BF44014BB06E" originalValue="Tkoč">Tkoc</normalizedToken>
and 
<normalizedToken id="3B1F6BA56FF91D337C00024613CE01DA" originalValue="Barták">Bartak</normalizedToken>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
). This species was collected from aspens fallen 8-10 years ago. The species did not show any preferences either to the trunk size or tree mortality mode (windfall vs. windbreak) Table 1. Its occurrence positively correlated with the following fungi: 
<taxonomicName id="9FF81A628A0DB86F6086674F077E53B8" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Fomitopsidaceae" genus="Fomitopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Fomitopsis pinicola" order="Polyporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="pinicola">Fomitopsis pinicola</taxonomicName>
(RS=0.99, P&lt;0.01), 
<taxonomicName id="9514105C446F7E3AE86BC074BD1BB63D" genus="Cerioporus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Cerioporus leptocephalus" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" rank="species" species="leptocephalus">Cerioporus leptocephalus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="649251FE2348ADBDED54B95A655E3568" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Polyporaceae" genus="Royoporus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Royoporus badius" order="Polyporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="badius">Royoporus badius</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="B657885350C1DF21265E7D9FA930267E" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Polyporaceae" genus="Trametes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Trametes trogii" order="Polyporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="trogii">Trametes trogii</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="A2BD1C6469CAD9BEBF6ACD17E60C0C0C" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Corticiaceae" genus="Punctularia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Punctularia strigosozonata" order="Corticiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="strigosozonata">Punctularia strigosozonata</taxonomicName>
(RS=0.73, P&lt;0.01), 
<taxonomicName id="52D88071AAFD13D3D61D3AF58582BC71" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Xenasmataceae" genus="Xenasma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Xenasma rimicola" order="Polyporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="rimicola">Xenasma rimicola</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2F6A08FD637E6B4F2818A342E5334FF2" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Kurtia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Kurtia argillacea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argillacea">Kurtia argillacea</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="9D8BECA89CC91EB0D1584DA89E42BD66" class="Agaricomycetes" genus="Resinicium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Resinicium bicolor" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="bicolor">Resinicium bicolor</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="880A41E826774CF239D874963B344C79" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Thelephoraceae" genus="Tomentella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Tomentella badia" order="Thelephorales" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="badia">Tomentella badia</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="347B118D74F88398915D27B6AB44447D" genus="T." lsidName="T. crinalis" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" rank="species" species="crinalis">T. crinalis</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="22FDD51A023F21C57878C0B002357ED4" genus="T." lsidName="T. lapida" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" rank="species" species="lapida">T. lapida</taxonomicName>
(RS=0.61, P&lt;0.05).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F7B5F7F81F5F9769B5C3614D5388C3EB" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="864EB8A65896D869BA32268E27DDC180" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175">Conservation</paragraph>
